HEADWORD: Amusive
<hw>A*mu"sive</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having power to
amuse or entertain the mind; fitted to excite mirth.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> -- <wordforms><wf>A*mu"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
-- <wf>A*mu"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
